<!--DOCTYPE section SYSTEM "file:/opt/share/xml/Oxygen/docbook/dtd/docbookx.dtd"--><ns4291:section xmlns:ns4291="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.platforms.linux.processControl.whatIsRunLevel">

  <ns4292:title xmlns:ns4292="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">What is a run-level</ns4292:title>
  <ns4293:para xmlns:ns4293="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns4294:emphasis xmlns:ns4294="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">A run-level is a specific configuration of processes.</ns4294:emphasis> Linux typically
    installs a number of standard process configurations, each starting a specified set
    of processes, including
    <ns4295:itemizedlist xmlns:ns4295="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      <ns4296:listitem xmlns:ns4296="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns4297:formalpara xmlns:ns4297="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns4298:title xmlns:ns4298="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Run-Level 0</ns4298:title>
        <ns4299:para xmlns:ns4299="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          This run-level requests system halt. 
        </ns4299:para>
      </ns4297:formalpara></ns4296:listitem>
      <ns4300:listitem xmlns:ns4300="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns4301:formalpara xmlns:ns4301="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns4302:title xmlns:ns4302="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Run-Level 1</ns4302:title>
        <ns4303:para xmlns:ns4303="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          This run-level provides single-user access without networking. It is mainly used
          for performing maintenance tasks on the local machine during which one wants to
          ensure that there are no other users busy on the machine (for example when
          attempting to fix a corrupted disk). Run level 1 only provides a single console.
        </ns4303:para>
      </ns4301:formalpara></ns4300:listitem>
      <ns4304:listitem xmlns:ns4304="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns4305:formalpara xmlns:ns4305="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns4306:title xmlns:ns4306="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Run-Level 2</ns4306:title>
        <ns4307:para xmlns:ns4307="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          This run-level provides multi-user mode without NFS.
        </ns4307:para>
      </ns4305:formalpara></ns4304:listitem>
      <ns4308:listitem xmlns:ns4308="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns4309:formalpara xmlns:ns4309="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns4310:title xmlns:ns4310="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Run-Level 3</ns4310:title>
        <ns4311:para xmlns:ns4311="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          This run-level provides multi-user mode with networking. It is often used for
          server configurations.
        </ns4311:para>
      </ns4309:formalpara></ns4308:listitem>
      <ns4312:listitem xmlns:ns4312="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns4313:formalpara xmlns:ns4313="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns4314:title xmlns:ns4314="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Run-Level 5</ns4314:title>
        <ns4315:para xmlns:ns4315="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          Multi-user mode with networking and <ns4316:command xmlns:ns4316="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">xdm</ns4316:command>. This
          run-level provides a graphical login (<ns4317:command xmlns:ns4317="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">gdm</ns4317:command> typically 
          used when running <ns4318:emphasis xmlns:ns4318="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">GNOME</ns4318:emphasis> as window manager
          and <ns4319:command xmlns:ns4319="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">kdm</ns4319:command> typically used when running 
          <ns4320:emphasis xmlns:ns4320="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">KDE</ns4320:emphasis>) and starts up <ns4321:command xmlns:ns4321="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">X</ns4321:command>
          with the chosen window manager.
        </ns4315:para>
      </ns4313:formalpara></ns4312:listitem>
    </ns4295:itemizedlist>
  </ns4293:para>
  <ns4322:para xmlns:ns4322="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    Run-levels 4 is typically used to set up a custom configuration. The advantage of using a separate
    run-level for customization is that one can easily revert to a standard run-level.
  </ns4322:para>
  <ns4323:para xmlns:ns4323="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    Run-level 6 controls the shutdown process. It specifies the order in which the processes are
    terminated.
  </ns4323:para>
</ns4291:section>